    <name>
      <text>Column vectors</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Given the column vectors \(\mathbf{a} = {@vec_a@}\) and \(\mathbf{b} = {@vec_b@}\), find the following:</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <li>
        <div>\( \mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</div>
    </li>
    <li>
        <div>\( {@k1@}\mathbf{a} - {@k2@}\mathbf{b} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</div>
    </li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p><b>Part (a)</b></p>
<p>To add column vectors, we add the corresponding components (top with top, bottom with bottom):</p>
\[ 
\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b} = {@vec_a@} + {@vec_b@} 
= \begin{pmatrix} {@ax@} + ({@bx@}) \\ {@ay@} + ({@by@}) \end{pmatrix} 
= {@ta1@} 
\]

<p><b>Part (b)</b></p>
<p>First, we multiply each vector by its scalar:</p>
\[ {@k1@}\mathbf{a} = {@k1@}{@vec_a@} = \begin{pmatrix} {@k1@} \times {@ax@} \\ {@k1@} \times {@ay@} \end{pmatrix} = {@step1_a@} \]
\[ {@k2@}\mathbf{b} = {@k2@}{@vec_b@} = \begin{pmatrix} {@k2@} \times {@bx@} \\ {@k2@} \times {@by@} \end{pmatrix} = {@step1_b@} \]

<p>Then we subtract the results:</p>
\[ 
{@k1@}\mathbf{a} - {@k2@}\mathbf{b} = {@step1_a@} - {@step1_b@} 
= \begin{pmatrix} {@k1*ax@} - ({@k2*bx@}) \\ {@k1*ay@} - ({@k2*by@}) \end{pmatrix} 
= {@ta2@} 
\]]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
